TO rebase my fork branch

 Add upstream (if not already added) check using git remote -v:
git remote add upstream https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt.git
Note:

git remote -v
origin    https://github.com/v-cshekar/sonic-mgmt.git (fetch)
origin    https://github.com/v-cshekar/sonic-mgmt.git (push)
upstream  https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt.git (fetch)
upstream  https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt.git (push)


1. Fetch the latest from both remotes:
 
   git fetch origin
   git fetch fork
 
2. Checkout your fork's master:
 
   git checkout -b master fork/master
   # or if you already have a local master branch:
   git checkout master
   git reset --hard fork/master
 
3. Rebase onto sonic-mgmt's master (origin):
 
   git rebase origin/master
 
4. Push the updated master back to your fork:
 
   git push fork master --force-with-lease

