  Sync Fork with Upstream

  Remotes:
  - origin = upstream (sonic-net/sonic-mgmt)
  - fork = your fork (v-cshekar/sonic-mgmt)

  ---
  1. Fetch latest changes from upstream:
  git fetch origin

  2. Checkout local master tracking origin/master:
  git checkout --track origin/master
  ▎ Use --track origin/master because both origin and fork have master, so git needs it specified explicitly.

  3. Push updated master to your fork:
  git push fork master

  4. Create and checkout a new branch:
  git checkout -b v-cshekar/your-branch-name

  5. Push new branch to your fork:
  git push fork v-cshekar/your-branch-name
